claim.claim-text:
An apparatus comprising: channel categorizing means (151) for categorizing on a per-user basis a channel quality information received from a user in a multi-carrier transmission system; and scheduling means (15) for individually selecting for said user one of a plurality of feedback overhead reduction techniques in response to a categorization output of said channel categorizing means (151);
wherein said scheduling means (15) is configured to select said one of said plurality of feedback reduction techniques from a group comprising at least two of a carrier restriction technique where transmission to and from said user is restricted to a single component carrier, a feedback compression technique where a channel quality feedback information for a plurality of component carriers allocated to said user is compressed, and a feedback bundling technique where a plurality of feedback signals used for acknowledging or non-acknowledging transmission over a plurality of component carriers allocated to said user is bundled into a single feedback signal; and
wherein said scheduling means (15) is arranged to apply said carrier restriction technique when said channel quality information exceeds a first threshold, wherein said scheduling means (15) is arranged to apply said feedback compression technique when said channel quality information does not exceed said first threshold but exceeds a second threshold, and wherein said scheduling means (15) is arranged to apply said feedback bundling technique when said channel quality information does not exceed said first and second thresholds but exceeds a third threshold.
